div1.p: At which office they consent that serivce of all subsequent papers, except writs and processes, may be made upon them
Service of within this day of 191 and recepit of a copy thereof, admitted, Attorneys for
In the United States District Court For The Western District of Washinton, Northern Division
In the Matter of the application of Francis Stephen Medcraf for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
MR GEO. D. EMERY, for the Petitioner
THE PETITIONER was charged and conviced before a Justice of the Peace with the 'crime' of practicing dentistry without a certificate' contrary to the provisions of the Dental Code of Washington.
